caption: I would give this place zero stars if I could. My wife and I both have Covid and are too tired to cook. I haven’t had Dominoes pizza in years and decided to order us a pizza. I placed the order at 7:10pm. It was scheduled to arrive by 8:30pm or so, which seemed like a long time, but we decided it was worth it. At 7:29 the tracker said the pizza was cooked and was being inspected. By 8:30 the tracker had not updated, so we called the place and were told “Soon, soon”. By 9pm we still didn’t have our order and called again. The man said the driver was on the way. At one point the tracker said he’d arrived but nobody was there. It got to be 9:45 and still no order. We tried to call again to cancel but nobody answered. At 10pm we got a call from the driver that he was outside, but we didn’t see anyone through the window. We told him it was too late, that we’d waited almost 3 hours and didn’t want the order anymore. The tracker then said “Order complete” even though we refused the order.

Order took one hour to arrive after showing order was complete food was cold and driver was rude telling me he called my phone 10 times which was untrue driver was given the wrong number will not order again they are highly expensive and the need to hire drivers that are not rude to their customers highly disappointed with this order:
I got the wrong order 😒 but that was a first

Delivery took more than an hour and the pizza was stale. And I ordered a Buffalo chicken pizza which comes with Buffalo sauce on the pizza but when i got my pizza there was no Buffalo sauce. I also ordered garlic sauce and didn’t even receive it. What a disappointment

Terrible place! Over an hour for delivery and food is alway like warm at best! Has happened last 5 or 6 times. Only reason kept ordering Is kids wanted to. Order your local Pizza joint...better food at half the price!
Waited almost an hour for a pick up that said it had been ready for 10 mins no one attempted to help me when I said I was there for pick up and they all just stood around looking at one another

Literally just read the other reviews. They’re all 100% accurate. This location claims to have COVID policies that prevent their drivers from delivering pizza to your door and instead make you meet them downstairs and outside, but in person?? The logic is entirely backwards and the management does not have any interest in customer’s safety or feedback here at this location.
Delicious !

(Translated by Google) Terrible, it is the third time that the order with the wrong ingredients has arrived wrong.  (Original) Pésimo, es la tercera vez que llega mal el pedido con los ingredientes equivocados.
It's Domino's. The restaurant itself is pretty clean. The service is good. At least from my dealings with them. They have good deals for carryout.

Both cooks were preparing food with their masks down and no gloves. They pulled them above their mouths (not noses) when they came up to the window to run my card but I don't feel awesome about eating food prepared with no attention to safety precautions with nearly 5.5k new covid cases in NYC yesterday alone.
If you're hungry it will do the trick, but nothing special
The food comes well packaged but for some reason, they always forget to pack the dipping cup(s). I’ve had this issue multiple times. Other than that, this branch is pretty decent.

Delivery man refuses to leave pizza with doorman. Wants to me to come out in the rain while I was on a work call and couldn’t. Called the store and manager giving me explanation about their policies and covid (bullshit), basically forces me to come in direct contact with their delivery man exposing me, completely irresponsible and unsafe during this time (they have to check them). Showed his anger at me over the phone. No contact free delivery.

Delivery driver did not hand off.. was very rude on the telephone.. and my pizza  left on boxes downstairs. Anyone could have taken my order. The delivery took 45 minutes only one block from my house,  I also tipped for this terrible service. I will think twice before ordering here again.

This location has employees JOKING about not wearing masks and gloves - while the food is being made and sent out. I ordered from here for pickup, watched in horror as an unmasked man made the food and another unmasked man took it out of the oven and shoved it (gloves-less) into the box. Demanded a refund and left hungry. Very disturbing! The corporate office should be reprimanding these types of offenders.

I literally live 2 blocks away from this particular Domino's store, According to their Domino's tracking on their app the order left at 9:57 p.m., and  It would arrive at 10:10 p.m. then it changed to 10:20pm.  Then again it change to 10:32 p.m., And again to 10:47 p.m., And yet again change to 10:53 p.m.. At this point I called the store had me waiting online before a human answered for 5 minutes. I explained according to their tracker the order left almost an hour ago why is it not here yet.  He Only said to me is the driver will be there in 2 minutes that was not true the finally showed up at 11:01. When the order arrived  The parmesan bites were burnt I also ordered a medium pizza with 3 toppings 2 toppings were completely missing. The barbecue chicken was cold the Italian sandwich was cold and the bread was burnt on the outside. And I live 2 blocks from this Domino's store. Store on 5th Avenue and 16th street Brooklyn new york. If I was able to give 0 stars to this Domino's door I would.  I call the store spoke to the manager his response was I'll give you a refund.  No I'm sorry let me try to make it right for you let me resend the order. nothing like that.  Don't feel like ever ordering  Domino's ever again .

Employee did not wear mask while talking to customer, seems like they don't care about other people life. Staff who worked in the kitchen non of them wearing mask except for one staff. One of them shows no respect for customer, the way he talked like we getting the food for free. Morever, Covid-19 is not a joke. Wear a mask while you deal with customer and making food, your joke can kill thousands of lives.

Just received my pizza. The pizza and the wings seemed old as if they popped the pizza out of the fridge, heated it up and gave it to me. The wings also seemed a day old and they just put some hot sauce on top to make it look new. Never eating at dominos again. Paid $40 what a waste of money.

I ordered a pizza for pick up online. I arrived a little early, so I waited in my car right outside of the store. Looking through the window I can see the person making pizzas was not wearing a mask. A few minutes later I entered the store. The aforementioned pizza maker greets me at the window still not wearing a mask. When I asked him about it, he gave me some lame excuse that he has to do everything in the store and wearing a mask hinders him. While he's taking care of my payment at the register, he's playing with his saliva on his lips. Never again.

I placed a carry out order. The workers and manager there weren't wearing any gloves or masks, they touched peoples phones, their own phones, credit cards, and more while handling food. Not only was this place very unsanitary but i had to wait more than an hour to get my food. This is very alarming especially in a time like this with Covid-19 going around. I am very upset and will never order from here again.

Placed a carry out order. The manager was the one who handed me the pizza...with no gloves on!! Handed it to me with no gloves and mouth cover around her chin. Never ordering g from here again. The absolute worst service of any food spot in Sunset Park. The staff does not even care to look at anyone waiting at the counter. I came in and waited in front of the counter to ask for a menu and even though multiple staff members walked past, none acknowledged me. It took 10 minutes to get a menu finally. After deciding, it took another 10 minutes until I finally left because no one would come to take my order. Other customers were waiting behind me. Another customer came up next to me and asked staff for a menu and without even looking up, they said, "no we don't got a menu." Why wouldn't Dominos have menus on hand?? I tried again to say I hadn't even made my order yet but the staff was simply not paying attention and so I just left after wasting 20 minutes there. I'm not saying anyone should be let go because everyone deserves to make an income, but it's so clear the staff absolutely does not care at all. They need serious training.

The only thing about this place that is most terrible is the online ordering process it is just so confusing for a first time online customer to navigate through. The company asks for explicit instructions to give to the driver in making an actual delivery. Being specific I found out if you're disabled, live in an apartment building and want your order delivered to your door no matter if you are in an elevator building.....the deliver guy will not deliver it directly to your apartment. The delivery person will  only remain downstairs in the vestibule of a dwelling. If you're alone and have no other person to call upon to get your delivery.....you are screwed. Be ware if you're layed up in bed and make an online order. This had to be written for those who are homebound and incapable of going downstairs to pick up their order. I write it as there's no documentation of this rule and you'd be surprised to find out after the fact.

Fairly consistent Domino's location when it comes to delivery time and pizza quality. Over the years, their quality and time has improved, with perfectly (as perfect as Domino's can get) cooked pizzas. Drivers still call you when they're outside in their car instead of calling when at the door, but I suppose that is the norm now.

I have been ordering from this location using the app for years and today was the last straw. They sent me the wrong item and I called the driver to rectify the issue and the store manager informed him that another driver would be sending my order (over 45min later). I  never received the original item I ordered since I had to leave for work. 1 hour to deliver the first time and another over 45 min wait to be told by the second driver that he’s on the way. I will longer be ordering from this location again and at this point there’s no need to spend my money at a business that doesn’t value their customers. I do not blame the drivers because it’s the store manager who should’ve been on the ball with the order and with reaching out to me on the status of the order, it takes but 2 minutes of their time to inform their customer of the issue.

I ordered through the app and I will never order to from this location again. I watched the tracker and it said it delivered but it didn’t arrive until about an hour later. I also asked for four blue cheeses and it never arrived, telling the driver to bring it back was pointless because at this rate we’ve been waiting for our food for about two hours and it was cold.  Calling the place is also a nightmare, since they never seem to pick up.
The staff here is friendly and the wait is never long if you are picking up. Delivery is not bad either, but then again im less than a mile away but never have waited much more than 30 minutes.

Dominos is the worst experience ever. I ordered pizza, there was a 4.00 delivery charge. Driver would NOT come up to apt. You had to meet him on the street. Then, they expect a tip on top of the awful service and 4.00 delivery charge. This is the worse pizza chain in the industry. The founders should  be ashamed of themselves.

I've been using this particular Dominos, located on 5th Ave and 15th st.  Park Slope Brooklyn for many years. For the most part when I order, its for delivery. My food always arrives in a reasonable amount of time, its hot and the drivers are friendly and deliver with a smile. The staff at the restaurant location are equally as friendly and courteous and never forget to offer up a friendly, "Enjoy your pizza" I definitely recommend this Slope Dominos  for either pick up or delivery in the hopes your experience will be as satisfying as my families experiences have been.ADDED COMMENT AT A LATER DATE  Extra acknowledgement for the.Dominoes Manager...... She really knows her stuff, always accommodating and if you are Lucky enough to have had your pizza prepared by her, you will experience Dominoes at it's VERY BEST

So far they have never gotten my order wrong and always has been warm & waiting for me ready to pick up when I get there. Pay accepted with credit or debit cards and cash. No parking lot or structure just street parking. Wheelchair accessible, but no seating available. This is pick up or delivery only.
I called them  to add something To my order a guy rudly told me no they didnt have it and hung up?! What kind of customer service is this?

I will never order from this Domino's or any Domino's again. After an uncomfortable exchange with the delivery driver staring at my girlfriend as she took the pizza out of his bag for him. She had to get a pen to sign her receipt. She felt bad that he had to walk up the stairs because he seemed off. So, she tipped him generously. He then proceeded to text her phone and tell her about his spiritual massage YouTube channel on which he frequently massages women's butt's in public. Instead of apologizing, the manager (I did not get her name) said that it's normal to hand out business cards. No. It's not. If any of my employees ever said that to one of our customers they wouldn't have a job. she neglected to apologize, or even offer a modicum of compassion. I followed up with the district supervisor (Islam). He did nothing. I reached out to customer service and they referred me back to him. Nothing has been done, and it's been weeks without an apology or compensation. If you like sexual harassment and uncomfortable exchanges this is the Domino's for you.

The sandwich ends up containing way more bread than meat , and some of the slices have literally only one small piece of chicken on it when it is supposed to be a topping.  That being said , none of this is a reflection upon the delivery drivers or the employees in general. I think the manager or dominos is dictating the portions they put on.

The food is good but, they need to have delivery when ordering from online. Why have an app where you can order but you have to get up and get your food? My local Dominos absolutely sucks. The pizza was undercooked (even though I asked for well done!) and the driver was a jerkoff. This was strike two. There is no strike three. Would have given zero stars but they won't let you. I am now a Papa Johns customer. Enjoy life.

The worst dominos ever...I explained that my pizza wasn't edible and was hung up on...ALWAYS USE YOUR CREDIT CARD for your protection with Dominos.  I am getting a refund through my card company...

The forgot to bring the dipping sauce which made the cheese nips bland.  I requested a bottle of diet coke and the driver brought a bottle of sprite.  The pizza was excellent just poor quality control.  They have some stupid delivery policy and are not aloud to enter an apartment building, so you need to go downstairs to meet the.  10 other places I order food from in Brooklyn bring the food to your door but Domino's cant take an elevator up a few floors.
Their pizza stink and isnt cut evenly and their hot wongs made me choke theyre drowned in vinegar

I had a friend staying with me once who was visiting from Chicago, and he drunkenly ordered from here at like 4am after I had gone to sleep because it was the only place still open. When I discovered what happened the next morning I felt embarrassed and ashamed for the both of us.

Domino's had this new advertising campaign where they go on about how much better their pizza is now, and that they totally revamped the process.  Even people that I know and in theory trust, said good things.  So I figured, why not, let's give it a shot.  Short version: Their pizza didn't change much.  If you liked it before, you'll probably like it now.  And if you liked it before, you should search for pizza, and find some with higher ratings, because they're better.  The sauce tasted vaguely improved from what it was, and that's about it.  Also, there's a delivery charge apart from the tip.  Really?  The terrible awful Papa John's has a stupid delivery charge too.  I guess all those places that talk about free delivery are actually saying "We're better than Domino's and Papa John's!"  Great.  The delivery guy was sort of dumb, though the online delivery that they have is actually cool.  And the pizza was edible, just not something that I'd ever choose.
